usually misspelled abroad), who at the trial came out quite irrelevantly with a poem of his own composition, a piece of jagged neurotic rhetorism extolling Skotoma because he



...taught us to worship the Common Man,

and showed us that no tree

can exist without a forest,

no musician without an orchestra,

no wave without an ocean,

and no life without death.



